You need to install Web Meta Language ( http://thewml.org/,
http://thewml.berlios.de/ ), Latemp ( http://web-cpan.berlios.de/latemp/ ),
Bundle::Latemp, as well as the following CPAN modules:

* IO::All

* Template::Preprocessor::TTML

* DateTime

* HTML::TokeParser Simple

* XML::LibXSLT

* WWW::Google::SiteMap

And the WML Extended APIs:

* http://svn.berlios.de/svnroot/repos/thewml/extended-apis/trunk/

How to build the homesite:
--------------------------

1. Install Subversion and run:

svn co http://stalker.iguide.co.il:8080/svn/shlomif-homepage/homepage/trunk/

2. Install perl 5.8.x in case it's not already installed. 

3. Run and configure CPAN (see - http://sial.org/howto/perl/life-with-cpan/) 
and type:

    $ perl -MCPAN -e 'install Task::Sites::ShlomiFish'

Or if you have CPANPLUS installed:

    $ perl -MCPANPLUS -e 'install Task::Sites::ShlomiFish'

4. Install Latemp:

    $ svn co http://svn.berlios.de/svnroot/repos/web-cpan/latemp/trunk/
    $ cd trunk/installer
    $ scons PREFIX="$HOME/apps/latemp/" install
    $ cd ../support-headers
    $ perl install.pl

5. Add Latemp to the beginning of your path:

    $ PATH="$HOME/apps/latemp/bin:$PATH"

6. 
    $ svn co http://stalker.iguide.co.il:8080/svn/shlomif-homepage/wml-affiliations/trunk/wml/
    $ cd trunk/wml
    $ bash Install.bash

7.
    $ svn co http://svn.berlios.de/svnroot/repos/thewml/extended-apis/trunk/
    $ cd trunk/xhtml/1.x/
    $ bash Install.bash

8. Do the following to build the site, after all dependencies were installed:

    $ svn co http://stalker.iguide.co.il:8080/svn/shlomif-homepage/homepage/trunk/
    $ ./gen-helpers.pl
    $ (cd t2/humour/fortunes/ && make)
    $ make

